HTML Shorthand Basics:

To create a tag:
tagName + enter/tab
ex:
h4 + enter =

<h4></h4>



To create multiple tags:
tagName*number + enter
ex:
h4*4 + enter:

<h4></h4>
<h4></h4>
<h4></h4>
<h4></h4>



To put something inside of a tag:
tagName{content} + enter
ex:
p{Stuff} + enter =

<p>Stuff</p>



To create another tag WITHIN a tag:
tagName>otherTagName + enter
ex:
div>div>h4>a + enter =

<div>
    <div>
        <h4>
            <a></a>
        </h4>
    </div>
</div>



To create multiple DIFFERENT tags all within the same tag:
tagName>tag1+tag2 + enter
ex:
div>h1+h2 + enter =

<div>
    <h1></h1>
    <h2></h2>
</div>



To create a tag with a Class:
tagName.className + enter
ex:
h1.coolClass + enter =

<h1 class="coolClass"></h1>

These stack too:
h1.coolClass.otherClass.anotherClass + enter =

<h1 class="coolClass otherClass anotherClass"></h1>



To create a tag with an ID:
tagName#className + enter
ex:
h1#coolId + enter = 
<h1 id="coolId"></h1>



All of this can 100% be used together, and are wonderful for notes. Heres a very good example of everything being used at once:

div.bestClass#bestId>div+h1{h1 contents}+p{Lorem GoesHere}+h3.okayClass.mehClass{More Lorem} + enter =

<div class="bestClass" id="bestId">
    <div></div>
    <h1>h1 contents</h1>
    <p>Lorem Goes Here</p>
    <h3 class="okayClass mehClass">More Lorem</h3>
</div>

Let me know if this makes sense, and if you need any further help, you can always slack me!
:)